RACE.RACE_TEXT: GULFSTREAM PARK RACE 11 1 1/16M All Weather Track CR: 95. Maiden Special Weight Purse 84000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 118 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: STANLEY HOUSE tracked in the four path, loomed up in the six path under a ride around the far turn, bid at the top of the lane, swept past an inner foe near the eighth pole, and drew clear in the final furlong. BEL AMI raced in the two path around the first turn and stalked in the three path down the backside, waited for room in the two path around the far turn, was roused passing the quarter pole and tipped out to the five path in upper stretch, and kept on for place. NATE THE GREAT prompted the pace in the four path, was cued to bid in the three path rounding the far turn, took a brief lead from the four path into the lane, but was quickly overtaken by the outer eventual winner, and evened out for show. SIMCOE bumped with an outer foe at the start, travelled up close in the five path, was under rousing in the four path around the far turn and tipped out to the six path into the stretch, but was one paced. RIGEL raced in the five path around the first turn and chased from the three path down the backside, was driven in the five path rounding the far turn, but flattened while drifting inwards in the stretch. LANIGAN was unhurried along the inside but never factored from out in the six path in the stretch. NANGA PARBAT (GB) got bumped between foes at the start, rated in the two path but was tired from the five path in upper stretch. MY FAVORITE TOPIC raced in midpack in the two path but was empty from the three path turning into the stretch. FULL COVERAGE set the pace inside but gaveway turning into the lane. VINCENZINO was behind from the two to four paths and never threatened. SILENT MODE broke in and bumped an inner foe, and never menaced around the two to four path.
